a)
the beam angle in steel used for manual ultrasonic testing with shear waves shall be nominally the same
as that used during the original automated test;

b)
scanning shall be carried out with ultrasonic beam propagation in circumferential or longitudinal directions
(or both);

e)
the width of the transducer, measured parallel to the major axis of the tube, used in the manual ultrasonic
test shall not exceed that used during the original automated test;
